additional_info:
1) font change (primary)
"/*font-family: Comic Sans MS !important;*/"
where if you remove the "/*" and "/* you get to convert the font in comics, making it even more readable.
2)font size (primary)
font-size: 185% !important;
line-height: 280% !important;
changing 185 increase/decrease the font size, the 285 is for the interline
3) side bar size (secondary)
width: 70% !important;
change  70 to increase/decrease the sidebar

css:
@-moz-document regexp(".*\.wordpress\.com.*")
  {
div#secondary{
width: 70% !important;
    }
div#primary{
width: 150% !important; 
  /*font-family: Comic Sans MS !important;*/
  font-size: 185% !important;
  line-height: 280% !important;
}
 #content h1{
     font-size: 175% !important;
}
  }
